text: Cancellaria jayana is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cancellariidae, the nutmeg snails. ==Description== The size of an adult shell varies between 18 mm and 25 mm ==Distribution== This species is distributed in the Pacific Ocean along Mexico and Panama. ==References== ==External links== * Category:Cancellariidae Category:Gastropods described in 1958
title: Cancellaria jayana
